nifold/ChartedSpace.html#ChartedSpace\">ChartedSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">H</span> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">inst_chart_E</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/ChartedSpace.html#ChartedSpace\">ChartedSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">H</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">I</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/IsManifold/Basic.html#ModelWithCorners\">ModelWithCorners</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span> <span class=\"fn\">H</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">inst_mani</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/IsManifold/Basic.html#IsManifold\">IsManifold</a> <span class=\"fn\">I</span> (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span>) <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">inst_tangent_findim</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">M</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/FiniteDimensional/Defs.html#FiniteDimensional\">FiniteDimensional</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/IsManifold/Basic.html#TangentSpace\">TangentSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">I</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span>)</span></span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> (max u v w)</div></div>","info":{"doc":"A pseudo-Riemannian metric of smoothness class `C^n` on a manifold `M` modelled on `(E, H)`\nwith model `I`. This structure defines a smoothly varying, non-degenerate, symmetric,\ncontinuous bilinear form `gₓ` of constant negative dimension on the tangent space `TₓM`\nat each point `x`. Requires `M` to be `C^{n+1}` smooth.\nThis structure formalizes O'Neill's Definition 3.1 (p. 54) of a metric tensor `g` on `M`\nas a \"symmetric non-degenerate (0,2) tensor field on M of constant index.\"\nEach `gₓ` is a scalar product (O'Neill, Definition 20, p. 47) on `TₓM`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Geometry/Metric/PseudoRiemannian/Defs.html#PseudoRiemannianMetric","kind":"structure","line":210,"name":"PseudoRiemannianMetric","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L210-L252"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Geometry/Metric/PseudoRiemannian/Defs.html#QuadraticForm.rankNeg_eq_zero\"><span class=\"name\">QuadraticForm</span>.<span class=\"name\">rankNeg_eq_zero</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddCommGroup\">AddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/Defs.html#Module\">Module</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/FiniteDimensional/Defs.html#FiniteDimensional\">FiniteDimensional</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">q</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/QuadraticForm/Basic.html#QuadraticForm\">QuadraticForm</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hq</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/QuadraticForm/Basic.html#QuadraticMap.PosDef\">QuadraticMap.PosDef</a> <span class=\"fn\">q</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">q</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Geometry/Metric/PseudoRiemannian/Defs.html#QuadraticForm.negDim\">negDim</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a positive definite quadratic form, the negative dimension (index) is zero.\nO'Neill states (p. 47) that \"ν = 0 if and only if b is positive semidefinite.\"\nSince positive definite implies positive semidefinite (Definitions 17 (1) and (2), p. 46),\na positive definite form must have index `ν = 0`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Geometry/Metric/PseudoRiemannian/Defs.html#QuadraticForm.rankNeg_eq_zero","kind":"theorem","line":153,"name":"QuadraticForm.rankNeg_eq_zero","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L153-L170"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Geometry/Metric/PseudoRiemannian/Defs.html#QuadraticForm.posDef_no_neg_weights\"><span class=\"name\">QuadraticForm</span>.<span class=\"name\">posDef_no_neg_weights</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddCommGroup\">AddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/Defs.html#Module\">Module</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">q</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/QuadraticForm/Basic.html#QuadraticForm\">QuadraticForm</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hq</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/QuadraticForm/Basic.html#QuadraticMap.PosDef\">QuadraticMap.PosDef</a> <span class=\"fn\">q</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">w</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Dimension/Finrank.html#Module.finrank\">Module.finrank</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span>)</span></span> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Sign/Defs.html#SignType\">SignType</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h_equiv</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/QuadraticForm/IsometryEquiv.html#QuadraticMap.Equivalent\">QuadraticMap.Equivalent</a> <span class=\"fn\">q</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/QuadraticForm/Basic.html#QuadraticMap.weightedSumSquares\">QuadraticMap.weightedSumSquares</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Dimension/Finrank.html#Module.finrank\">Module.finrank</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span>)</span></span>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">w</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span></span></span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Dimension/Finrank.html#Module.finrank\">Module.finrank</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">w</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Sign/Defs.html#SignType.neg\">SignType.neg</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A positive definite quadratic form cannot have any negative weights\nin its diagonal representation. A quadratic form `q` derived from a bilinear form `b`\nis positive definite if `b(v,v) > 0` for `v ≠ 0` (O'Neill, Definition 17 (1), p. 46).\nThe existence of a negative weight would imply `q(v) < 0` for some `v ≠ 0`, a contradiction. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Geometry/Metric/PseudoRiemannian/Defs.html#QuadraticForm.posDef_no_neg_weights","kind":"theorem","line":139,"name":"QuadraticForm.posDef_no_neg_weights","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L139-L151"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Geometry/Metric/PseudoRiemannian/Defs.html#QuadraticForm.neg_weight_implies_neg_value\"><span class=\"name\">QuadraticForm</span>.<span class=\"name\">neg_weight_implies_neg_value</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddCommGroup\">AddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/Defs.html#Module\">Module</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">q</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/QuadraticForm/Basic.html#QuadraticForm\">QuadraticForm</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">w</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Dimension/Finrank.html#Module.finrank\">Module.finrank</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span>)</span></span> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Sign/Defs.html#SignType\">SignType</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h_equiv</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/QuadraticForm/IsometryEquiv.html#QuadraticMap.Equivalent\">QuadraticMap.Equivalent</a> <span class=\"fn\">q</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/QuadraticForm/Basic.html#QuadraticMap.weightedSumSquares\">QuadraticMap.weightedSumSquares</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Dimension/Finrank.html#Module.finrank\">Module.finrank</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span>)</span></span>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">w</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span></span></span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Dimension/Finrank.html#Module.finrank\">Module.finrank</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span>)</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hi</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">w</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Sign/Defs.html#SignType.neg\">SignType.neg</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">v</span> : <span class=\"fn\">E</span>), <span class=\"fn\">v</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">q</span> <span class=\"fn\">v</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"When a quadratic form is equivalent to a weighted sum of squares,\nnegative weights correspond to vectors where the form takes negative values.\nThis is a concrete realization of a 1-dimensional negative definite subspace,\ncontributing to O'Neill's index `ν` (Definition 18, p. 47). ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Geometry/Metric/PseudoRiemannian/Defs.html#QuadraticForm.neg_weight_implies_neg_value","kind":"theorem","line":105,"name":"QuadraticForm.neg_weight_implies_neg_value","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L105-L137"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Geometry/Metric/PseudoRiemannian/Defs.html#QuadraticForm.QuadraticMap.weightedSumSquares_basis_vector\"><span class=\"name\">QuadraticForm</span>.<span class=\"name\">QuadraticMap</span>.<span class=\"name\">weightedSumSquares_basis_vector</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddCommGroup\">AddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/Defs.html#Module\">Module</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">weights</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Dimension/Finrank.html#Module.finrank\">Module.finrank</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span>)</span></span> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Dimension/Finrank.html#Module.finrank\">Module.finrank</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span>)</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">v</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Dimension/Finrank.html#Module.finrank\">Module.finrank</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span>)</span></span> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hv</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">j</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Dimension/Finrank.html#Module.finrank\">Module.finrank</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span>)</span></span>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">v</span> <span class=\"fn\">j</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#ite\">if</a> <span class=\"fn\">j</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">i</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#ite\">then</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#ite\">else</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/QuadraticForm/Basic.html#QuadraticMap.weightedSumSquares\">QuadraticMap.weightedSumSquares</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">weights</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">v</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">weights</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a standard basis vector in a weighted sum of squares, only one term in the sum\nis nonzero. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Geometry/Metric/PseudoRiemannian/Defs.html#QuadraticForm.QuadraticMap.weightedSumSquares_basis_vector","kind":"theorem","line":90,"name":"QuadraticForm.QuadraticMap.weightedSumSquares_basis_vector","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L90-L103"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Geometry/Metric/PseudoRiemannian/Defs.html#QuadraticForm.negDim\"><span class=\"name\">QuadraticForm</span>.<span class=\"name\">negDim</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddCommGroup\">AddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/Defs.html#Module\">Module</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/FiniteDimensional/Defs.html#FiniteDimensional\">FiniteDimensional</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">q</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/QuadraticForm/Basic.html#QuadraticForm\">QuadraticForm</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The negative dimension (often called the index or negative index of inertia) of a\nquadratic form `q` on a finite-dimensional real vector space.\n\nThis value is defined by diagonalizing the quadratic form into an equivalent\n`QuadraticMap.weightedSumSquares ℝ s`, where `s : Fin (finrank ℝ E) → SignType`\nassigns `1`, `0`, or `-1` to each component. The `negDim` is the count of\ncomponents `i` for which `s i = SignType.neg`.\n\nBy Sylvester's Law of Inertia, this count is an invariant of the quadratic form.\nGeometrically, `negDim q` represents the dimension of any maximal vector subspace\non which `q` is negative definite. This corresponds to O'Neill's Definition 18 (p. 47)\nof the index `ν` of a symmetric bilinear form `b` on `V`, which is \"the largest integer\nthat is the dimension of a subspace `W ⊂ V` on which `b|W` is negative\ndefinite.\" ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Geometry/Metric/PseudoRiemannian/Defs.html#QuadraticForm.negDim","kind":"def","line":67,"name":"QuadraticForm.negDim","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L67-L88"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Analysis.InnerProductSpace.Basic","Mathlib.Analysis.RCLike.Lemmas","Mathlib.Geometry.Manifold.MFDeriv.Defs","Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.BilinearForm.Properties","Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.QuadraticForm.Real","Mathlib.Topology.LocallyConstant.Basic"],"instances":[{"className":"CoeFun","name":"PseudoRiemannianMetric.coeFunInst","typeNames":["PseudoRiemannianMetric"]}],"name":"PhysLean.Mathematics.Geometry.Metric.PseudoRiemannian.Defs"}